**Exploring packaging scripts**

I’m considering if afterSign always runs, even without a signature, but I think our script bypasses missing credentials. If the credentials are there but the app isn't signed, notarization fails, which seems good to me. 

I’m looking at packaging the script with "npm run build" and "electron-builder." I need to ensure the build happens right after afterSign. Using node to modify package JSON while keeping it intact might require applying a patch. I’ll also need to set up a build folder and insert the afterSign setting properly in the config.
